RESIDENTS of Imbali in Pietermaritzburg, KZN, laida complaint after hearing screeching tyres in their neighbourhood. Patrolling cops dispatched to Imbali unit 2 heard gunshots when they got to Vimbukhalo Road. Colonel Thembeka Mbele said: “Allegedly, a man among the group of people fired shots at the police. “Other units also responded and a search was conducted with the assistance of the canine unit.” A 35-year-old suspect in a taxi was bust after he was found in possession of an illegal firearm and ammunition. A taxi was also impounded. The suspect will appear in the Pietermaritzburg Magistrates Court tomorrow on charges of attempted murder, possession of an illegal firearm and ammunition, and discharging a firearm in public.